@node MS-Dos disks
@section How do I Read and write MS-Dos disks?
@cindex MS-Dos disks
@cindex CrossDos
@cindex Msh
No problem for owners of Workbench 2.1 or higher: The program CrossDos is
part of the Workbench. All you have to do is mounting the device @file{pc0:}
by putting it into the drawer @file{Devs:DOSDrivers} or by double-clicking
the icon in @file{Sys:Storage/DOSDrivers}. Ms-Dos disks in drive @file{df0:}
can now be handled in the usual manner replacing the word @file{df0:} by
@file{pc0:}. For example the directory can be shown with the command
@t{dir pc0:}.

People still running Workbench 2.0 or lower need a program called @code{MSH}.
You will find this on the Aminet (directory misc/emu) and on Fish disk 382.
@xref{Sources}. After editing the file @file{devs:MountList} as described in
the documentation you have to say @t{Mount msh:} in the CLI and can now do
the same as above replacing the word @file{pc0:} with @file{msh:}.

