@node Splitting
@section How do I split large files?
@cindex Splitting files
There are some archives which are too large to fit on one disk. To transfer
them on disks you need to split them into smaller pieces and transfer each
part on a separate disk. I recommend Martin Schlodder's @code{Splitter}.
(Aminet, @file{util/misc/splitter_121.lha}. The archive contains binaries
for MS-DOS and should be compilable without problems on any Unix system.


@node Mailing lists
@section Discussing things
@cindex Mailing lists
A mailing list is a server that allows to discuss special things via
Email. The server holds a list of people that are interested in the
respective topic. For example, the gcc mailing list will discuss bugs,
new features and other problems of gcc. (@pxref{Compilers}) If a mail is
sent to the server from someone he will forward this mail to all the
other people on the list.

You will be added to the list by sending a mail to the server which will
usually contain the word @samp{Subscribe} or something similar. Once you
are no more interested in the mailing list you can unsubscribe.

Unforunately the servers have a different syntax of subscribing and
unsubscribing. The best way to find how to subscribe is to send a mail
with the word @samp{Help} to the server. He will reply a mail which
should explain how to handle this special server.

